{
  "texts": [
    "This issue is specifically detrimental during the downstream task, where the model underperforms on actual data due to significant differences in the transformed and original input data, regardless of having a converged contrastive loss.",
    "Masked Auto Encoders (MAEs) [9], as illustrated in Figure 2, is a generative/masking method designed to understand the underlying structure of unlabeled data by reconstructing it based on partial views.",
    "A linear projector first transforms the input data into a fixed-size representation.",
    "Most of the projected inputs are randomly selected and masked during this process.",
    "This masking is done using learnable mask tokens, which are vectors of the same length as the transformed input."
  ]
}